A motorcyclist was crushed to death on Friday in a road accident that occurred in Gbongan, Osun State. The rider, whose name could not be ascertained, was travelling along Gbongan-Ife Expressway when he reportedly wrongly overtook a truck, thereby resulting in the crash. The spokesperson for the Osun sector command of the Federal Road Safety Corps, Agnes Ogungbemi, said the accident occurred around 4:40pm. She said, “The accident occurred along Gbongan-Ile-Ife road. It was caused by wrongful overtaking. It involved an Iveco Eurostar truck and a Jincheng motorcycle. The motorcycle wrongly overtook the truck. One person, a male, was killed but two other people involved were not injured. “The family of the deceased took over the remains of the victim, while the vehicle involved was taken over by the police in Gbongan.”  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com